<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 07 at 11:32PM MDT  by NWS Pueblo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Kiowa
and northeastern Crowley Counties through 1215 AM MDT...
At 1132 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a  group of strong
thunderstorms 12 miles southwest of Wild Horse Point, or 33 miles
north of La Junta, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Arlington.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 400 AM MDT for
southeastern Colorado.</instruction>
